## Checking disease/condition categories
colData(oral) |>
  as.data.frame() |>
  distinct(study_condition, disease)

Algorithm used: metadata extraction and category search
colData(oral) = extracts sample information from the microbiome obect
as.data.frame() = converts the metadata into a normal R dataframe
distinct(study_condition, disease) = searches for unique combinations of study condition and disease
Purpose: to check whether the dataset has enough disease groups for comparison
-Fit for linear regression model which the regression only works if there are at least two disease categories

