## Bray-Curtis PCoA plot

altExps(oral) <- splitByRanks(oral)

oral_pcoa <- oral |>
  runMDS(
    FUN = vegdist,
    method = "bray",
    exprs_values = "relative_abundance",
    altexp = "genus",
    name = "BrayCurtis"
  )

plotReducedDim(
  oral_pcoa,
  "BrayCurtis",
  colour_by = "disease",
  shape_by = "study_condition"
) +
  labs(
    x = "PCo 1",
    y = "PCo 2",
    title = "Oral community composition by disease condition"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

Algorithm used: ecological distance calculation and dimensionality reduction.
splitByRanks(oral) = groups bacteria by taxonomic rank, such as genus.
altExps(oral) =  stores those taxonomic-rank versions inside the microbiome object.
vegdist(method = "bray") = calculates Bray-Curtis distance between samples.
-Bray-Curtis distance measures how different two microbiome communities are based on bacterial abundance.
runMDS() = reduces the complex microbiome dataset into two main coordinates.
plotReducedDim() = plots those coordinates as a 2D graph.
colour_by = "disease" --colors samples by disease group.
shape_by = "study_condition" --changes point shape by study condition.

Purpose: to visualize whether oral microbiome samples cluster differently based on disease or condition.
Why it matters: this analyzes the whole bacterial community, not just one species.

